  "extras": {
    "summary": "AN ACT TO AUTHORIZE THE BOARD OF SUPERVISORS OF JACKSON COUNTY, MISSISSIPPI, TO CREATE A PUBLIC IMPROVEMENT DISTRICT UNDER CHAPTER 31, TITLE 19, MISSISSIPPI CODE OF 1972; TO AUTHORIZE THE DISTRICT TO IMPOSE AND COLLECT A RETAIL ASSESSMENT WITHIN THE DISTRICT; TO PROVIDE THAT THE PROCEEDS OF THE RETAIL ASSESSMENT MAY BE USED AND PLEDGED, TOGETHER WITH SPECIAL ASSESSMENTS AND OTHER REVENUES AUTHORIZED UNDER CHAPTER 31, TITLE 19, MISSISSIPPI CODE OF 1972, FOR THE PURPOSES SET FORTH IN CHAPTER 31, TITLE 19, MISSISSIPPI CODE OF 1972; TO REQUIRE THAT AN ELECTION BE HELD FOR THE IMPOSITION OF THE RETAIL ASSESSMENT; TO PROVIDE FOR COLLECTION AND DISBURSEMENT OF THE RETAIL ASSESSMENT BY THE DISTRICT; TO REQUIRE SEPARATE ACCOUNTING AND AN ANNUAL AUDIT; AND FOR RELATED PURPOSES."
  },
